com.here.mobility.sdk.map

Class UserLocationMarkerManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.here.mobility.sdk.map.UserLocationMarkerManager

  • public class UserLocationMarkerManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Responsible for the user location marker, which is drawn on the map to indicate the user's location.

    • Method Detail

      • setLocationSource

        public void setLocationSource(@Nullable
                              UserLocationSource locationSource)
        Sets the source of user locations. You may use null only while the marker mode is UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode.MARKER_HIDDEN.

      • setDeviceDirectionSource

        public void setDeviceDirectionSource(@Nullable
                                     DeviceDirectionSource directionSource)
        Sets the source for device direction. You may use null only while the marker mode is not UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode.DIRECTIONAL_MARKER_VISIBLE.

      • setLocationAndAngleApplier

        public void setLocationAndAngleApplier(@NonNull
                                       UserLocationMarkerManager.LocationAndAngleApplier applier)
        Sets the object responsible for applying the user locations and device direction to the user location marker. Use UserLocationMarkerManager.resetToDefaultLocationApplier() to use the default applier.

      • resetToDefaultLocationApplier

        public void resetToDefaultLocationApplier()
        Resets to the default applier, which simply sets the location on the marker via Marker.setPoint(LatLng) and the angle via Marker.setAngle(float).

      • setMarkerMode

        public void setMarkerMode(@NonNull
                          UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode markerMode)
        Sets the mode of the user location marker. Note that to use a mode other than UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode.MARKER_HIDDEN, you must first set a non-null user location source via UserLocationMarkerManager.setLocationSource(UserLocationSource). Likewise, to use UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode.DIRECTIONAL_MARKER_VISIBLE, you must first set a non-null direction source via UserLocationMarkerManager.setDeviceDirectionSource(DeviceDirectionSource)

      • setNonDirectionalMarker

        public void setNonDirectionalMarker(@NonNull
                                    Marker marker)
        Sets the marker to display when in UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode.NON_DIRECTIONAL_MARKER_VISIBLE mode. Use UserLocationMarkerManager.resetToDefaultNonDirectionalMarker() to use the default one.

      • resetToDefaultNonDirectionalMarker

        public void resetToDefaultNonDirectionalMarker()
        Resets the non-directional marker to the default one.

      • setDirectionalMarker

        public void setDirectionalMarker(@NonNull
                                 Marker marker)
        Sets the marker to display when in UserLocationMarkerManager.MarkerMode.DIRECTIONAL_MARKER_VISIBLE mode. Use UserLocationMarkerManager.resetToDefaultDirectionalMarker() to use the default one.

      • resetToDefaultDirectionalMarker

        public void resetToDefaultDirectionalMarker()
        Resets the non-directional marker to the default one.

      • getVisibleMarker

        public Marker getVisibleMarker()
        Returns the currently displayed marker; null if none.
